net.heroicefforts.viable.android.rep.it
Class GIssueTrackerRepository

java.lang.Object
  net.heroicefforts.viable.android.rep.it.GIssueTrackerRepository
All Implemented Interfaces:
Repository
public class GIssueTrackerRepository
extends Object
implements Repository

This is the repository implementation that bridges to the Google Issue Tracker. Viable client applications that wish to register their I.T. project should add lines similar to those found below:

   <meta-data android:name="viable-provider" android:value="Google" />
   <meta-data android:name="viable-project-name" android:value="<your project name, defined after the /p/ in Google's URL>" />
   <meta-data android:name="viable-project-description" android:value="A description of your project." />
   <meta-data android:name="viable-project-lead" android:value="<Your Name>" />
   <meta-data android:name="viable-project-versions" android:value="1.0.0, 1.1.0" />

Author:
jevans
